        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Being that it hasn't been mentioned yet, I'll take a second to note a fairly important factor when engaging rhag2: GRC.  Rhag2 (Rhag`Mozdezh) casts a naughty curse/dot spell.  The spell drops atk, mana, and a nasty DoT to boot on those affected.  This doesn't really mean much to us, as we most likely wont be getting aggro, however to your MT/MA this is definately an issue. (main tank/main assist, whatever it's referred to on your server)  Rhag1 drops a spell called "Greater Remove Curse" (GRC) which will, as you're hopefully guessing, cure that spell.  My guild took both rhags out last night with two people casting GRC on the tank.  Without GRC, your MT stands no chance of holding aggro, and your raid will likely wipe quickly.</P><P>I think all the info here is correct, but if it's wrong please post to let us know where I facked it.</P><P></P><P>".. I'm not handicapped, I just walk with a pimp limp."</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=135581">Philiac Shroudbearer</a><BR>58 necro of Dark Aegis<BR>Fennin Ro<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
